CD Cargo Plans to Bid for Polish Cargo Unit, E15 Reports

-- B y   L e n k a   P o n i k e l s k a
-- 
2011-03-28T08:17:26Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-28/cd-cargo-plans-to-bid-for-polish-cargo-unit-e15-reports.html
Czech state-owned rail cargo
company CD Cargo AS plans to bid for a majority stake in the
cargo unit of Polskie Koleje Pantswowe, or Polish state
railways,  E15  reported, citing the company.  The 50 percent plus one share stake in the Polish company
may be worth up to 13 billion koruna ($746 million), the
newspaper added.  To contact the reporter on this story: 
Lenka Ponikelska in Prague 
 lponikelska1@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at   jagomez@bloomberg.net . 